HEADWORD: Chylaqueous
<hw>Chy*la"que*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Chyle</ets> + <ets>aqueous</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Consisting of chyle much diluted with water; -- said of a liquid
which forms the circulating fluid of some inferior animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chyle</ent>⟦br⟧
